<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="82" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1895,2030]" pageId="11" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1895,1922]" pageId="11" pageNumber="82">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Well characterized by almost rectangularly-bent crossvein dm-cu, setulose anepisternum and anepimeron, lack of subalar setae, and hyaline wing with several isolated dark spots.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="84" pageId="11" pageNumber="82" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1895,2030]" pageId="11" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1968,1994]" pageId="11" pageNumber="82">Remarks</emphasis>
. Of the 7 described species, 4 are known from the Palearctic Region (2 restricted to the Palearctic Region and 2 known from both the Palearctic and Nearctic Regions), and 3 are restricted to the Nearctic Region.
</paragraph>
<caption box="[151,1087,2005,2030]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366723/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="83" startId="12.[151,264,2005,2030]" targetBox="[165,1390,181,1958]" targetPageId="12">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1087,2005,2030]" box="[151,1087,2005,2030]" pageId="12" pageNumber="83">
FIGURES 25–32. Characters and morphological terms of the family 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Seguy" baseAuthorityYear="1934" box="[894,1029,2005,2030]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Sciomyzidae</taxonomicName>
(IV).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,153,359]" pageId="13" pageNumber="84">
Before our study, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1838" box="[398,471,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Elgiva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[398,471,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="84">Elgiva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was known from 
<collectingCountry box="[671,742,153,179]" name="China" pageId="13" pageNumber="84">China</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Rozkosny, R. &amp; Knutson, L." box="[751,1073,153,179]" pageId="13" pageNumber="84" pagination="65 - 69" refId="ref15416" refString="Rozkosny, R. &amp; Knutson, L. (1991) Two new species of Sciomyzidae (Diptera) from Palaearctic China. Entomotaxonomia, 13 (1), 65 - 69." type="journal article" year="1991">Rozkošný &amp; Knutson (1991)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rozkosny &amp; Knutson" authorityYear="1991" box="[1193,1407,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Elgiva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="manchurica">
<emphasis box="[1193,1407,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="84">Elgiva manchurica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a new species from 
<collectingCountry box="[373,440,189,215]" name="China" pageId="13" pageNumber="84">China</collectingCountry>
on the basis of a male from Harbin, 
<collectingRegion box="[849,1102,189,215]" country="China" name="Heilongjiang" pageId="13" pageNumber="84">Heilongjiang Province</collectingRegion>
(Palearctic Region of 
<collectingCountry box="[1353,1425,189,216]" name="China" pageId="13" pageNumber="84">China</collectingCountry>
). In our study we did not find 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rozkosny &amp; Knutson" authorityYear="1991" box="[480,647,225,251]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Elgiva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="manchurica">
<emphasis box="[480,647,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="84">E. manchurica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but we found 
<specimenCount box="[821,908,225,251]" pageId="13" pageNumber="84" type="male">2 males</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount box="[965,1078,225,251]" pageId="13" pageNumber="84" type="female">3 females</specimenCount>
, also from 
<collectingRegion box="[1206,1355,225,251]" country="China" name="Heilongjiang" pageId="13" pageNumber="84">Heilongjiang</collectingRegion>
, which belong to 2 other species, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Harris, 1780)" authorityName="Harris" authorityYear="1780" baseAuthorityName="Harris" baseAuthorityYear="1780" box="[444,725,261,287]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Elgiva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="solicita">
<emphasis box="[444,557,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="84">E. solicita</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Harris, M." box="[572,717,261,287]" pageId="13" pageNumber="84" pagination="73 - 166" refId="ref13785" refString="Harris, M. (1780) An exposition of English insects with curious observations and remarks, wherein each Insect is particularly described; its Parts and Properties considered; the different Sexes distinguished, and the Natural History faithfully related. Decads III. V. Robson, London, 73 - 166, 50 pls." type="book chapter" year="1780">Harris, 1780</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Loew, 1845)" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1845" baseAuthorityName="Loew" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[784,1042,260,287]" class="Insecta" family="Sciomyzidae" genus="Elgiva" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="divisa">
<emphasis box="[784,882,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="84">E. divisa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Loew, H." box="[897,1033,260,287]" pageId="13" pageNumber="84" refId="ref14617" refString="Loew, H. (1845) (Dipterologischer Beitrag). [Ersten Theil]. [Zu der]. Offentlichen Prufung den Schuler der Koniglichen Friedrich Wilhelms Gymnasium zu Posen. W. Decker &amp; Comp., Posen, 52 pp., 1 pl." type="book" year="1845">Loew, 1845</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, both new to 
<collectingCountry box="[1193,1264,261,287]" name="China" pageId="13" pageNumber="84">China</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
